{"article_id":"R2dDltYmgyb6aYEx","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Enjoy those tax cuts","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"while you have them :","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"The Republican tax bill would deliver average initial tax cuts for Americans across all income lines ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"but by 2027 , that would n't be the case .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Within a decade , the tax bill would boost average levies for everyone","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"earning up to $ 75,000 ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"which includes most taxpayers ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"Congress ' nonpartisan tax analyst estimated Monday .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"The projection seemed unlikely to have any impact on the fate of the legislation ,","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"which was expected to win House approval Tuesday .","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"Senate passage was likely by Wednesday","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"as the GOP races to send President Donald Trump his first major legislative victory before Christmas .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"The $ 1.5 trillion tax package would lower many tax brackets","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"and limit or reduce popular deductions , changes","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"that are likely to impact almost every American .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"While middle-class taxpayers are expected to see small tax breaks ,","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"the big winners would be wealthy Americans ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"including President Donald Trump ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"who will enjoy a windfall for his real estate empire .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"If the bill is signed before the end of the year ,","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"taxpayers would likely feel the impact in a few weeks , most likely by February .","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"The tax bill also lowers the corporate tax rate , a change","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that will remain in place","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"even as individual tax cuts expire .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"`` Most of the individual changes in the bill are set to expire after 2025 ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"while the corporate provisions are generally permanent , ''","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"wrote Nancy Vanden Houten , senior economist at Oxford Economics , in a research note .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"`` Many individuals will receive tax cuts ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"but others will face tax increases ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"particularly after individual tax cuts expire . ''","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"The Joint Committee on Taxation calculated","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"that in 2019 , people","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"earning $ 20,000 to $ 50,000","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"would see tax cuts","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"averaging 10 percent or more .","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"Those","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"making $ 200,000 to $ 1 million","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"would see reductions","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"averaging slightly less .","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"But by 2023 , people","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"making under $ 30,000","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"would see tax increases","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"while those","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"earning more","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"would see their tax cuts get smaller .","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"That pattern would continue .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"In 2027 , a year","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"after most individual tax provisions expire ,","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"people","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"making up to $ 75,000","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"would be paying more on average than under current law .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"The committee says","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"around 118 million of the 177 million tax returns are from households","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"making up to $ 75,000 .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"Republicans ended the individual tax cuts in 2026","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"to conform to Senate rules","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"that require the measure","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"to limit the federal debt increases","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"it would cause .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"The bill is projected to boost federal shortfalls by nearly $ 1.5 trillion over the coming decade .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"GOP lawmakers say","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"they 'd expect a future Congress to continue the tax cuts","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"so they wo n't expire .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"If achieved ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"that would drive up deficits even further .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"A separate study by the Tax Policy Center , a private nonpartisan group , found","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"that individual taxes would be reduced on average next year by $ 1,600 .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"But that ranged on average from $ 60 for people","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"earning below $ 25,000","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"to $ 7,640 for those","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"making above $ 149,000 .","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"Those in the top 1 percent ,","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"earning over $ 733,000 ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"would see average tax cuts of $ 51,140 .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"In 2027 , 53 percent of families would face tax increases","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"averaging $ 180 .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"Those tax boosts on average would grow with income ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"the policy center said .","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"One in four taxpayers that year would have tax reductions","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"averaging $ 1,540 ,","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"with larger cuts for higher-earning people .","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"Most of the bill 's benefits go to businesses and the wealthy ,","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"which","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"Republicans say","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"would goose the economy","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"and benefit all .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"Democrats reject that assertion","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"and are expected to oppose the bill unanimously .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"On Monday , moderate Sen. Susan Collins , R-Maine , said","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"she 'd support the bill ,","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"meaning all voting Republicans are expected to back it , enough for passage .","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Sen. John McCain , R-Ariz. , is at home","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"battling brain cancer","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"and is expected to miss the vote .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"The GOP controls the Senate 52-48 .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":189,"left":96,"right":188,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":96,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":105,"right":187,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":101,"right":104,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":97,"right":100,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":100,"left":99,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":98,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":102,"right":103,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":102,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":113,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":111,"right":112,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":111,"left":107,"right":110,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":12,"right":106,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":106,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearit